# Example Apache / Phusion Passenger snippets for Node behind a domain or subdomain.
# cPanel often generates its own `.htaccess` when you use “Setup Node.js App” — use this only
# if your host documents manual Passenger configuration.
#
# Copy relevant lines into the DOCUMENT ROOT that maps to your app (adjust paths).

# PassengerNodejs /home/USERNAME/nodevenv/repositories/APP/20/bin/node
# PassengerAppRoot /home/USERNAME/repositories/bw-maintenance
# PassengerAppType node
# PassengerStartupFile server/src/index.js

# If the panel expects the startup file under app root only:
# PassengerStartupFile src/index.js
# (and set PassengerAppRoot to .../bw-maintenance/server)
